      "problemTitle": "Why does skin get stressed so easily here?",
      "problemBody": "<p>Changing weather is brutal on the skin barrier. Cold air, wind, and low humidity raise transepidermal water loss, so skin loses moisture faster than it can hold on to it. That’s why your face can feel tight after a walk by Lake Vättern or after hours in heated indoor air.</p><p>Mainstream skincare often answers with strong cleansers, acids, and too many actives. But a barrier that is already under pressure does not need more aggression. Research on barrier function consistently shows that over-cleansing and frequent exfoliation can worsen irritation, especially when temperature swings and wind are already in the picture.</p><p>In Jönköping, recovery matters more than performance. The forests of Småland may feel fresh on your skin, but your skin often reads the same weather as dry, windy, and exposing. If you want calmer skin, reduce friction first. Add support before you add more “treatment.”</p>",
