      "problemTitle": "Why does skin get out of balance in Växjö?",
      "problemBody": "<p>Växjö’s mix of forest humidity, lake climate and urban air can seem gentle, but skin experiences it as constant switching. Moist air outside and dry heat indoors can disrupt the barrier, increase water loss and make skin more reactive. Once the barrier is stressed, everything feels harsher: cleansing stings, creams sit wrong and redness shows up faster.</p><p>The usual response is often to go harder. People reach for stronger cleansers, more acids and extra exfoliation when skin feels oily or congested. But barrier research keeps pointing the same way: too much stripping and friction can worsen sensitivity instead of fixing it. Skin is not being difficult; it is trying to protect you.</p><p>In a green city like Växjö, with water nearby and weather that keeps changing, the problem is rarely “not enough actives.” It is usually not enough respect for what skin is dealing with. Less punishment, more support. That shift alone can change everything.</p>",
